  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="72fd-de9f-10dd-1ac1" name="MRC Body Armour" hidden="false">
      <description>A Team with MRC Body Armour rolls a die when they fail a Save for a Hit from an Artillery Bombardment (after any re-rolls). On a roll of 5+, they are unharmed. On any other roll, they are Destroyed as usual after any necessary Firepower rolls.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f4e8-d94a-6fee-09fc" name="Close Assault" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry teams carried as Passengers in a Ram Kangaroo can Dismount in the Assault Step when Charging into Contact. Passengers cannot Assault if the vehicle moved at Dash Speed.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="097e-e610-0f21-5ee9" name="One Use" hidden="false">
      <description>A Unit with Tulip can only fire one Artillery Bombardment per game.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ba7f-f677-5ed7-7c52" name="Saturation Bombardment" hidden="false">
      <description>Each Saturation Bombardment weapon counts as two weapons firing in an Artillery Bombardment.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="042b-756f-9830-f952" name="Bunker Killer" hidden="false">
      <description>Bunker Killer Teams can hit Nest and Bunker Teams despite being an Artillery Bombardment. As a Brutal Bombardment, any Infantry, Gun (including Nests and Bunkers), or Unarmoured Tank Teams it hits must re-roll succesful Saves.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f8f9-4e77-067e-4afb" name="Petard" hidden="false">
      <description>When firing a Bombardment with their Petard, AVRE Teams:
-may spot and fire Bombardments even if they moved this turn,
-do not need to re-roll successful To Hit for only having 1 or 2 weapons firing, and
-ignore the Danger Close rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ce66-3b20-db4c-8c86" name="Mike Target" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Spotting Team successfully Rages In an Artillery Unit with Mike Target, they may immediatly roll to Range In another Artillery Unit. If successful, the additional Artillery Unit is treated as Ranging In on the same attempt as the first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="66f9-6b33-7661-f029" name="Gigantic" hidden="false">
      <description>Gigantic Units cannot be placed in buildings and cannot be placed from Ambush within 16&quot;/40cm of enemy Teams.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b482-3435-c988-8c54" name="Air Observer Post" hidden="false">
      <description>An Air Observer Post is an Aircraft that arrives on a roll of 3+ (rather than the usual 4+)

An Air Observer Post is unarmed, but can act as an Observer Spotting for an Artillery Bombardment with an Aiming Pont within 12&quot;/30cm of tha Aircraft. The opposing player may shoot at the Aircraft immediately before it rolls to Range In as though the aircraft was Shooting.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a790-1a49-0725-721f" name="Airborne" publicationId="10a4-8008-66c3-952e" hidden="false">
      <description>This Formation may make an Airborne Assault in missions that use the Airborden Assault rules (page 84)</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9380-406b-d566-df3a" name="Night Attack" hidden="false">
      <description>If a Force with Night Attack is the attacker in a mission where the defender has Minefields, the player may attack at night. If they do so, Night Fighting rules (see page 113 of the rulebook) are in effect at the start of the game.

British Units from a Formation with  Night Attack can move freely from the start of the game. Friendly Units from other Formations or Support may not more out of their Deployment Area untill morning breaks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="1c8f-29ec-365d-4fe8" name="Flame Trailers" hidden="false">
      <description>Flame tanks cannot Charge into Contact and cannot Hold Objectives.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2e3b-3c59-067a-2fe1" name="Pioneers" hidden="false">
      <description>Pioneers Teams cross Minefields safely on a roll of 2+. If they remain in the Minefield and are not Pinned Down, they may clear the Minefield automatically in their next turn.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
